subsection.def:
cause
                    (訴訟) means a matrimonial cause as defined by
                    section 2 of the Ordinance;

paragraph.content:
in the case of an application under section 12 of the
                        Ordinance, a cause in which the respondent has not given notice of intention
                        to defend within the time limited;

subparagraph.content:
a cause to which rule 18(4) applies and in which no
                            notice has been given under that rule or any notice so given has been
                            withdrawn;

particulars of any circumstances which may assist the court in
                        determining whether there is a reasonable probability of reconciliation
                        between the parties;

paragraph.content:
where any party has given notice of intention to defend,
                                        fix the time within which his answer must be filed or
                                        amended;

an estimate of the probable length of the
                    trial;
                    and

that no application for such an order as is mentioned in
                    subparagraph
                    (b) is pending;

that the judge has made an order under section 18(1) of the
                    Matrimonial Proceedings and Property Ordinance (Cap.
                        192);

an order for maintenance pending suit;
                         (L.N. 135
                            of 1972)

a periodical payments order;
                         (L.N. 135
                            of 1972)

a secured periodical payments order;
                         (L.N. 135
                            of 1972)

a lump sum order;
                         (L.N. 135
                            of 1972)

a settlement of property order;
                         (L.N. 135
                            of 1972)

a transfer of property order;
                         (L.N. 135
                            of 1972)

any person who has obtained leave to intervene in the cause
                for
                the purpose of applying for the custody of a child of the family;

in the case of an application for a variation of settlement order, the
                    trustees of the settlement and the settlor if
                    living;

subsection.def:
judgment
                    debtor
                    (判定債務人) means a person liable under an order;

paragraph.content:
whether any and, if so, what debts are owing to the judgment
                    debtor;
                    and

subparagraph.content:
any travelling expenses paid to the judgment
                        debtor;
                        and

if the judgment creditor is represented by a solicitor, such sums as
                        the court may order in respect of the solicitor’s
                        charges;

if the judgment creditor is represented by a solicitor without counsel,
                        such sum as the court may order in respect of the solicitor’s
                        charges;
                        and

paragraph.content:
the discharge of any person
                    committed;
                    or

subsection.continued:
may be made to the registrar who may make such order on the application as he
                thinks fit or may refer the application or any question arising thereon to a judge
                for his decision. (L.N. 135 of 1976)

paragraph.content:
the residence of the parties to the agreement immediately before the death
                    and, unless both parties were then resident in Hong Kong, the domicile of the
                    applicant at that time;
